Package: dsdep
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, bash (>= 4.0), git, curl, python3 (>= 3.8), systemd
Recommends: python3-pip, python3-venv
Suggests: anaconda | miniconda3
Description: Data Science Deployment Tool for Linux
 dsdep is a command-line tool that automates the deployment of Python/Data
 Science projects on Linux servers with systemd service hardening.
 .
 Features:
  - Clone Git repositories automatically
  - Set up Python environments (conda or venv)
  - Install dependencies from requirements.txt
  - Create systemd service with auto-restart capability
  - Monitor application logs and restart on hang
  - Verify deployment status
 .
 This tool is designed for production deployment of ML/AI applications
 that need to run as persistent services with automatic recovery.
